00:14:25,000 --> 00:14:28,000
 But because of that, that land was always seen as cursed.

226
00:14:28,000 --> 00:14:34,000
 It was a place of great fire before where the worst of humanity took place.

227
00:14:34,000 --> 00:14:39,000
 The evils. If you could think about it, what's the worst thing that humanity could do?

228
00:14:39,000 --> 00:14:42,000
 Somebody taking their child and burning them in this fire.

229
00:14:42,000 --> 00:14:44,000
 Well, this is what Gehenna represented.

230
00:14:44,000 --> 00:14:48,000
 Now, in James' time, they're not doing that anymore, but here's what happened.

231
00:14:48,000 --> 00:14:55,000
 All of the rubbish, all of the stuff from Jerusalem that was rubbish, was sent down to Gehenna and was burnt there.

232
00:14:55,000 --> 00:15:01,000
 So fires within this forest were still happening, and the stench of that on the wrong day,

233
00:15:01,000 --> 00:15:04,000
 of the windmills blowing the wrong way, could still reach into Jerusalem.

234
00:15:04,000 --> 00:15:10,000
 It was a place that represented the stench of the worst of humanity. Does that make sense?

235
00:15:10,000 --> 00:15:13,000
 Now, follow James' argument here.

236
00:15:13,000 --> 00:15:17,000
 He's talking about the tongue, and he's comparing the tongue in the mouth

237
00:15:17,000 --> 00:15:24,000
 to the horrors of the reality of what happened in the past in Gehenna.

238
00:15:24,000 --> 00:15:30,000
 And he says, literally like this, "You've got to understand that this is what the tongue can do.

239
00:15:30,000 --> 00:15:38,000
 It can create a reality in which the worst of human choices become true."

240
00:15:38,000 --> 00:15:39,000
 Are you following?

241
00:15:39,000 --> 00:15:44,000
 This is the seriousness of what James is trying to talk to the church about.

242
00:15:44,000 --> 00:15:49,000
 Your tongue can, if not controlled, be like Gehenna.

243
00:15:49,000 --> 00:15:57,000
 It can actually create a situation where the worst of human choices become a reality.

244
00:15:57,000 --> 00:16:06,000
 So for James, right up front, our tongue, what we speak, and the reality of something created come together.

245
00:16:06,000 --> 00:16:07,000
 Are you following this?

246
00:16:07,000 --> 00:16:11,000
 Now, it's important that you see this link, because ultimately what James is trying to do

247
00:16:11,000 --> 00:16:16,000
 is kind of bring the church to a much bigger picture of what's happening in Scripture

248
00:16:16,000 --> 00:16:20,000
 around this idea of speaking and creating.

249
00:16:20,000 --> 00:16:23,000
 In fact, in verse 11, he speaks about the source.

250
00:16:23,000 --> 00:16:27,000
 He says, "Can fresh water and salt water come together and be in the same thing?

251
00:16:27,000 --> 00:16:29,000
 Can you have two sources creating two different things?"

252
00:16:29,000 --> 00:16:33,000
 He's like, "No, no, no, no. There's only one source."

253
00:16:33,000 --> 00:16:38,000
 So to understand really what James is trying to teach about this fact that our tongue can create realities

254
00:16:38,000 --> 00:16:45,000
 that would express the worst of what humanity can do, you have to take him all the way back to the source.

255
00:16:45,000 --> 00:16:50,000
 And I want to show you some things here from the source of our words.

256
00:16:50,000 --> 00:16:55,000
 And of course, to do that, you have to go all the way back to the right to the beginning of the biblical story.

257
00:16:55,000 --> 00:16:58,000
 Let me read you just the first three verses of Genesis.

258
00:16:58,000 --> 00:17:00,000
 Genesis 1, verses 1 to 3.

259
00:17:00,000 --> 00:17:04,000
 "In the beginning, God created the heavens and the earth.

260
00:17:04,000 --> 00:17:08,000
 Now the earth was formless and empty, and darkness was over the surface of the deep,

261
00:17:08,000 --> 00:17:12,000
 and the Spirit of God was hovering over the waters."

262
00:17:12,000 --> 00:17:18,000
 Verse 3, "And God said, 'Let there be light.' And there was light."

263
00:17:18,000 --> 00:17:19,000
 This is one of the most wonderful moments.

264
00:17:19,000 --> 00:17:25,000
 I wonder if you've ever asked yourself, "Why does God use words to create?"

265
00:17:25,000 --> 00:17:31,000
 Why does it specifically say here that God said He spoke, the Hebrew word here meaning literally out loud,

266
00:17:31,000 --> 00:17:33,000
 He spoke out loud, "Let there be light."

267
00:17:33,000 --> 00:17:34,000
 And there was light.

268
00:17:34,000 --> 00:17:35,000
 Think about this.

269
00:17:35,000 --> 00:17:39,000
 There was no one around right now in creation to hear it.

270
00:17:39,000 --> 00:17:40,000
 Come on, church.

271
00:17:40,000 --> 00:17:42,000
 Like no one had been created yet.

272
00:17:42,000 --> 00:17:45,000
 There were no animals, no things, no people.

273
00:17:45,000 --> 00:17:46,000
 That all comes later.

274
00:17:46,000 --> 00:17:47,000
 No one is there to hear it.

275
00:17:47,000 --> 00:17:50,000
 So why didn't He think creation into being?

276
00:17:50,000 --> 00:17:51,000
 Like what was the point?

277
00:17:51,000 --> 00:17:53,000
 What was the purpose of Him speaking?

278
00:17:53,000 --> 00:17:59,000
 God is trying to show us that there is a reality through the way in which He's created the words.

279
00:17:59,000 --> 00:18:07,000
 And so He stands over creation, and He speaks to this formless void, and He brings it into creation.

280
00:18:07,000 --> 00:18:14,000
 The Hebrew word that is found in the Old Testament that we translate to word in English is "deba."

281
00:18:14,000 --> 00:18:21,000
 And "deba" literally in the Hebrew can mean a word or it can mean a thing.

282
00:18:21,000 --> 00:18:22,000
 And those two things seem quite different.

283
00:18:22,000 --> 00:18:26,000
 Like is it a word or is it a thing, like a real thing?

284
00:18:26,000 --> 00:18:35,000
 Well, the reason why it can mean both is because in the Hebrew concept of the idea of a word, words have material reality to them.

285
00:18:35,000 --> 00:18:38,000
 This is different for us and how we think about it these days.

286
00:18:38,000 --> 00:18:44,000
 Because when we think about words, we just think about things that are spoken out of somebody's mouth or something written on a page.

287
00:18:44,000 --> 00:18:46,000
 The Hebrews didn't think of it that way.

288
00:18:46,000 --> 00:18:53,000
 Because God created with His word, the way they saw it is that God "debarred" creation.

289
00:18:53,000 --> 00:18:57,000
 Words, in other words, have material reality to them.

290
00:18:57,000 --> 00:19:01,000
 They can literally create something.

291
00:19:01,000 --> 00:19:06,000
 And this idea of the Hebrew concept of "deba" is found throughout our scriptures.

292
00:19:06,000 --> 00:19:11,000
 Have you ever heard someone say, "Man, when they talked, their words had weight."

293
00:19:11,000 --> 00:19:14,000
 That's the Hebrew idea of the concept of "deba."

294
