 When I was 15 years old, I decided to try out for the local play that was happening in my school.

295
00:19:20,000 --> 00:19:22,000
 I'd never done any drama before.

296
00:19:22,000 --> 00:19:26,000
 I'd never thought about doing drama, but I needed to get a few extra things on my resume.

297
00:19:26,000 --> 00:19:29,000
 So I decided I was going to be in the drama.

298
00:19:29,000 --> 00:19:31,000
 So I went along for the audition.

299
00:19:31,000 --> 00:19:33,000
 The drama teacher, who was like, "Why are you here?"

300
00:19:33,000 --> 00:19:35,000
 And I'm like, "Hi."

301
00:19:35,000 --> 00:19:37,000
 And he's like, "Okay, well here's what you need to do."

302
00:19:37,000 --> 00:19:40,000
 And he said, "I'm going to put a mirror on the front of the stage.

303
00:19:40,000 --> 00:19:46,000
 And then you're going to get up, and I want you to mime for five minutes the mirror and your interaction with the mirror."

304
00:19:46,000 --> 00:19:48,000
 So I was like, "Okay."

305
00:19:48,000 --> 00:19:51,000
 So I got up on stage, and there was the mirror.

306
00:19:51,000 --> 00:19:54,000
 And I went up, and I started interacting with the mirror, and I did all these things.

307
00:19:54,000 --> 00:19:58,000
 And I tried my best. It probably wasn't the greatest thing that had ever happened.

308
00:19:58,000 --> 00:20:04,000
 But as I put down the mirror at the end of the five minutes, I just stood there, and he didn't say anything.

309
00:20:04,000 --> 00:20:06,000
 He just sort of stared at me for a while.

310
00:20:06,000 --> 00:20:08,000
 And I was a little bit worried to begin with.

311
00:20:08,000 --> 00:20:10,000
 He was like just staring me down.

312
00:20:10,000 --> 00:20:12,000
 And then he said these words.

313
00:20:12,000 --> 00:20:18,000
 He said, "What you just did made me come alive."

314
00:20:18,000 --> 00:20:26,000
 I wonder if you can imagine for a 15-year-old kid, for somebody who's in authority, to say something like that over them.

315
00:20:26,000 --> 00:20:33,000
 And I remember in that moment thinking to myself, "That's what I want to do for the rest of my life."

316
00:20:33,000 --> 00:20:42,000
 Not drama, because I'm not great at drama, but I want to help people come alive.

317
00:20:42,000 --> 00:20:47,000
 That man didn't know it, but he dabbared on me in that moment.

318
00:20:47,000 --> 00:20:52,000
 A word out of his mouth gave this 15-year-old a calling for the rest of his life.

319
00:20:52,000 --> 00:21:00,000
 And ever since that day, I have been dedicating my life to helping people come alive.

320
00:21:00,000 --> 00:21:03,000
 This is the Hebrew concept of dabbar.

321
00:21:03,000 --> 00:21:07,000
 Our words have weight and material reality to them.

