00:22:50,000 --> 00:22:55,000
 Have you ever wondered why God asked Adam to name the animals?

347
00:22:55,000 --> 00:23:01,000
 It's because God is saying, "The first thing I want humanity to do is debar."

348
00:23:01,000 --> 00:23:03,000
 Are you following this?

349
00:23:03,000 --> 00:23:08,000
 "I want you to speak the name," name in the Hebrew being character,

350
00:23:08,000 --> 00:23:11,000
 "I want you to describe, I want you to tell the animals who they are."

351
00:23:11,000 --> 00:23:13,000
 That's essentially what he's asking Adam to do.

352
00:23:13,000 --> 00:23:16,000
 "Tell the animals who they are."

353
00:23:16,000 --> 00:23:19,000
 So there's Adam, and this weird creature comes before him,

354
00:23:19,000 --> 00:23:23,000
 and he looks at the creature, and he sees the tail, and he sees the big mane of hair,

355
00:23:23,000 --> 00:23:26,000
 and he goes, "Lion."

356
00:23:26,000 --> 00:23:27,000
 Are you with me?

357
00:23:27,000 --> 00:23:30,000
 Notice, Adam does not think lion.

358
00:23:30,000 --> 00:23:33,000
 Adam speaks the word.

359
00:23:33,000 --> 00:23:34,000
 He names the animal.

360
00:23:34,000 --> 00:23:38,000
 Lion, giraffe, alligator, whatever it was, whatever came before him,

361
00:23:38,000 --> 00:23:41,000
 whatever the Lord brought to him, he spoke out.

362
00:23:41,000 --> 00:23:47,000
 And in speaking out, he debarred on that animal, its character, its nature, its identity, what it is.

363
00:23:47,000 --> 00:23:48,000
 He gave it its name.

364
00:23:48,000 --> 00:23:53,000
 God is creating a structure where he creates, he speaks, he creates, he blesses,

365
00:23:53,000 --> 00:23:55,000
 and everything is declared good.

366
00:23:55,000 --> 00:23:57,000
 We then get to speak.

367
00:23:57,000 --> 00:23:58,000
 We get to create.

368
00:23:58,000 --> 00:23:59,000
 We get to bless.

369
00:23:59,000 --> 00:24:03,000
 And we get to bring the world into a flourishing that is very good.

370
00:24:03,000 --> 00:24:05,000
 Are you following this?

