00:28:38,000 --> 00:28:43,000
 "And the word was with God, and the word was God, and he was with God in the beginning.

448
00:28:43,000 --> 00:28:49,000
 Through him all things were made. Without him nothing was made that has been made."

449
00:28:49,000 --> 00:28:55,000
 And then if you jump down to verse 14, it says, "The word became flesh and made its dwelling amongst us."

450
00:28:55,000 --> 00:28:57,000
 So there's this beautiful thing.

451
00:28:57,000 --> 00:28:59,000
 Here's John trying to describe Jesus.

452
00:28:59,000 --> 00:29:06,000
 He's like, "You've got to understand that Jesus is the culmination of what every deba of God looks like."

453
00:29:06,000 --> 00:29:08,000
 Like if you were to take a human being,

454
00:29:08,000 --> 00:29:11,000
 one who was able to live every word and promise of God,

455
00:29:11,000 --> 00:29:15,000
 and everything that came out of his mouth was a blessing and not a curse,

456
00:29:15,000 --> 00:29:18,000
 it would be Jesus.

457
00:29:18,000 --> 00:29:20,000
 He is the word of God.

458
00:29:20,000 --> 00:29:22,000
 The fullness of creation is within him.

459
00:29:22,000 --> 00:29:27,000
 He was the one who was there, speaking at the beginning, creating it all in the first place.

460
00:29:27,000 --> 00:29:29,000
 And literally, John will go on to say this,

461
00:29:29,000 --> 00:29:33,000
 "Through his death, life, and resurrection, you yourself can become a new creation.

462
00:29:33,000 --> 00:29:35,000
 You yourself can be made new."

463
00:29:35,000 --> 00:29:38,000
 There is great hope in that, but you have to understand the starting point.

464
00:29:38,000 --> 00:29:42,000
 You want to understand who Jesus is? He's the deba of God.

465
00:29:42,000 --> 00:29:45,000
 God's word made flesh.

466
00:29:45,000 --> 00:29:48,000
 That's deba, materiality.

467
00:29:48,000 --> 00:29:53,000
 God speaks. Jesus is.

468
00:29:53,000 --> 00:29:56,000
 And in the fullness of that, it's quite interesting, because I love this phrase,

469
00:29:56,000 --> 00:30:00,000
 "And the word became flesh."

470
00:30:00,000 --> 00:30:03,000
 Now, follow with this.

471
00:30:03,000 --> 00:30:10,000
 There's only ever one time where the fullness of the word of God became flesh, and that's Jesus.

472
00:30:10,000 --> 00:30:15,000
 But I think words become flesh all the time.

473
00:30:15,000 --> 00:30:22,000
 I bet every single person in here can probably testify to a moment where someone said something over you,

474
00:30:22,000 --> 00:30:25,000
 spoke a word to you, maybe in a season in your life in the past,

475
00:30:25,000 --> 00:30:28,000
 maybe when you were young as a child, maybe it's even somebody in the office recently.

476
00:30:28,000 --> 00:30:34,000
 Someone said something to you, and it's deeply disrupted you, and it's deeply hurt,

477
00:30:34,000 --> 00:30:41,000
 and that word begins to take on flesh, and that flesh becomes you.

478
00:30:41,000 --> 00:30:47,000
 Maybe someone said to you, "You're not good enough. You're not good enough."

479
00:30:47,000 --> 00:30:50,000
 Maybe your parents said that to you when you were a kid,

480
00:30:50,000 --> 00:30:57,000
 or maybe a trusted authority figure, teacher, or a pastor, or a mentor said those words over you.

481
00:30:57,000 --> 00:30:59,000
 And here's what happened when they said those words to you.

482
00:30:59,000 --> 00:31:03,000
 You began to internalize the reality that nothing you could do could ever be good enough,

483
00:31:03,000 --> 00:31:07,000
 that no matter how many grades, how much effort, your parents never seemed to be satisfied,

484
00:31:07,000 --> 00:31:10,000
 never seemed to be pleased with you, and you kind of found yourself thinking,

485
00:31:10,000 --> 00:31:13,000
 "Well, I'm never going to be good enough at all."

486
00:31:13,000 --> 00:31:17,000
 And because that's been internalized, years later, you're still living a life

487
00:31:17,000 --> 00:31:20,000
 that when you're in relationships with the people around you,

488
00:31:20,000 --> 00:31:22,000
 you're not expecting that relationship to go well.

489
00:31:22,000 --> 00:31:25,000
 You're not expecting them to accept you, love you, embrace you,

490
00:31:25,000 --> 00:31:29,000
 because you are thinking, "I'm never going to be enough for my wife, for my husband,

491
00:31:29,000 --> 00:31:33,000
 for my boss, for my colleague, for my friends at church. I'm never enough."

492
00:31:33,000 --> 00:31:38,000
 And the word that was spoken has become flesh, and that flesh is now you.

493
00:31:38,000 --> 00:31:40,000
 Are you with me?

494
00:31:40,000 --> 00:31:45,000
 Or maybe somebody said over you, "You're never going to amount to anything."

495
00:31:45,000 --> 00:31:48,000
 And they immediately cast your future into doubt.

496
00:31:48,000 --> 00:31:52,000
 So then every time a job comes up, and you're like, "Man, should I apply for that?"

497
00:31:52,000 --> 00:31:56,000
 You're thinking, "Hang on a sec. I'm never going to amount to anything."

498
00:31:56,000 --> 00:31:58,000
 And you're suddenly feeling imposter syndrome.

499
00:31:58,000 --> 00:32:02,000
 "Oh, this is not for me. Somebody else is better at this than I am."

500
00:32:02,000 --> 00:32:06,000
 And it's stopping you from actually taking the risk to step into the one thing that God has created you for,

501
00:32:06,000 --> 00:32:09,000
 but you're staying away from it, because somebody at some point told you,

502
00:32:09,000 --> 00:32:11,000
 "You're never going to amount to anything."

503
00:32:11,000 --> 00:32:14,000
 And now you feel like an imposter all the time, no matter what it is that you try to do.

504
00:32:14,000 --> 00:32:20,000
 The word became flesh, and that flesh became you.

505
00:32:20,000 --> 00:32:23,000
 The reality is we do this to one another, don't we?

506
00:32:23,000 --> 00:32:26,000
 We speak slander and gossip and harsh words.

507
00:32:26,000 --> 00:32:29,000
 We use our tongue in such destructive ways.

508
00:32:29,000 --> 00:32:34,000
 We've been hurt, and here's the reality. Hurt people hurt people.

509
00:32:34,000 --> 00:32:36,000
 And because we've been hurt, and because somebody said that to us,

510
00:32:36,000 --> 00:32:40,000
 we've found ourselves saying that to somebody else.

511
00:32:40,000 --> 00:32:43,000
 And it seems that there's this cycle going on, and James writes to the church,

512
00:32:43,000 --> 00:32:50,000
 and he says, "It's like the fire of Gehenna is coming out of our mouths."

513
00:32:50,000 --> 00:33:00,000
 When we were created for communion and intimacy, we're just destroying everything.

514
00:33:00,000 --> 00:33:04,000
 Have a look at some of these other words that get spoken over us.

515
00:33:04,000 --> 00:33:11,000
 Perhaps some of these resonate with you and your journey.

516
00:33:11,000 --> 00:33:18,000
 And then James, in the moment of all of this, he says perhaps the strongest thing he says in this part.

517
00:33:18,000 --> 00:33:22,000
 Verse 9 and 12, he says, "With the tongue we praise our Lord and Father,

518
00:33:22,000 --> 00:33:26,000
 and then with it we curse people who have been made in God's likeness.

519
00:33:26,000 --> 00:33:29,000
 Out of the same mouth comes praise and cursing.

520
00:33:29,000 --> 00:33:31,000
 My brothers and sisters, this should not be.

521
00:33:31,000 --> 00:33:34,000
 Can both fresh water and salt water flow from the same spring?

522
00:33:34,000 --> 00:33:37,000
 My brothers and sisters, can a fig tree bear olives?

523
00:33:37,000 --> 00:33:39,000
 A grapevine bear figs?

524
00:33:39,000 --> 00:33:41,000
 And can salt spring produce fresh water?"

525
00:33:41,000 --> 00:33:43,000
 James says, "Look, we have to understand.

526
00:33:43,000 --> 00:33:47,000
 We can see the power of the destructive words of the enemy,

527
00:33:47,000 --> 00:33:50,000
 and we all have felt and experienced those words spoken over us."

528
00:33:50,000 --> 00:33:53,000
 But James is like, "Here's the reality. We all struggle with this.

529
00:33:53,000 --> 00:33:56,000
 We do both ourselves.

530
00:33:56,000 --> 00:34:00,000
 We come in, and we worship Him, and we praise Him, and we lift our hands up,

531
00:34:00,000 --> 00:34:04,000
 and we say, 'Oh, yes, Lord. Everything I am submitted to You.'"

532
00:34:04,000 --> 00:34:08,000
 And then on Monday, we start to slander and gossip and speak down,

533
00:34:08,000 --> 00:34:11,000
 and we start to criticize and judge, and then we come back on Sunday,

534
00:34:11,000 --> 00:34:13,000
 and we praise Jesus again.

535
00:34:13,000 --> 00:34:16,000
 And James is saying, "Hang on a second.

536
00:34:16,000 --> 00:34:21,000
 Can't you realize that that God process that leads to goodness

537
00:34:21,000 --> 00:34:24,000
 and that satanic evil process that leads to death,

538
00:34:24,000 --> 00:34:29,000
 don't you realize that both of these are coming out of your mouth?"

539
00:34:29,000 --> 00:34:32,000
 And that's why he then challenges the church, and he says,

540
00:34:32,000 --> 00:34:37,000
 "We all struggle with this, so the thing we have to do is check the source."

541
00:34:37,000 --> 00:34:40,000
 Because he says, "Can fresh and salt come out of the same source?"

542
00:34:40,000 --> 00:34:44,000
 They cannot. So the issue here is not behavior modification.

543
00:34:44,000 --> 00:34:49,000
 How do I say nice to things? The issue here, what is going on in my heart?

544
00:34:49,000 --> 00:34:54,000
 Because what's in here is obviously impacting what's coming out of here.

545
00:34:54,000 --> 00:34:57,000
 Jesus, in Luke 6, verse 45, He says,

546
00:34:57,000 --> 00:35:02,000
 "Out of the overflow of the heart, the mouth speaks."

547
00:35:02,000 --> 00:35:04,000
 So when James is saying, "We have to get back to the source,"

548
00:35:04,000 --> 00:35:07,000
 he's basically saying, "Look at your heart," but remember, he's doing it pastorally.

549
00:35:07,000 --> 00:35:10,000
 He's like, "Look at your heart.

550
00:35:10,000 --> 00:35:16,000
 What is going inside of your heart that's causing stuff to be happening?"

551
00:35:16,000 --> 00:35:20,000
 And it's almost like he's saying, "Look, we've got to invite the Holy Spirit

552
00:35:20,000 --> 00:35:24,000
 to constantly be examining our heart, because if it's true

553
00:35:24,000 --> 00:35:27,000
 that our words can bring life or death in us or through us,

554
00:35:27,000 --> 00:35:31,000
 then we have to constantly invite the Holy Spirit to be in our hearts,

555
00:35:31,000 --> 00:35:36,000
 because the health of my heart will determine the grace of my words."

556
00:35:36,000 --> 00:35:41,000
 You following? The health of my heart will determine the grace of my words.

557
00:35:41,000 --> 00:35:43,000
 So the question I should be asking myself is,

558
00:35:43,000 --> 00:35:46,000
 "What's really going on in my heart?"

559
00:35:46,000 --> 00:35:50,000
 I want to say two things predominantly go on in our hearts

560
00:35:50,000 --> 00:35:55,000
 that cause our words to align more with the evil side than with God's side.

561
00:35:55,000 --> 00:35:58,000
 Sin and hurt.

562
00:35:58,000 --> 00:36:03,000
 And those two things are constantly grappling in our heart.

563
00:36:03,000 --> 00:36:07,000
 Sin is such a reality for us all.

564
00:36:07,000 --> 00:36:12,000
 Jesus was one that lived a certain life that shows us a different way.

565
00:36:12,000 --> 00:36:14,000
 1 Peter 2.22, Peter writes this beautiful thing.

566
00:36:14,000 --> 00:36:18,000
 Let me read this to you in 1 Peter 2.22.

567
00:36:18,000 --> 00:36:22,000
 He says, speaking of Jesus, "He committed no sin, so no deceit was found in him."

568
00:36:22,000 --> 00:36:26,000
 Isn't that beautiful? "No deceit was found in his mouth," Peter said,

569
00:36:26,000 --> 00:36:27,000
 because he committed no sin.

570
00:36:27,000 --> 00:36:30,000
 So Peter makes this connection between the heart and the mouth.

571
00:36:30,000 --> 00:36:33,000
 He makes the connection with Jesus and says he's the only one.

572
00:36:33,000 --> 00:36:35,000
 Remember James at the beginning of the passage,

573
00:36:35,000 --> 00:36:39,000
 "If you were a perfect person, and good things always came out of your mouth,

574
00:36:39,000 --> 00:36:40,000
 but none of us are perfect."

575
00:36:40,000 --> 00:36:43,000
 So James is like, "None of us are Jesus."

576
00:36:43,000 --> 00:36:46,000
 So we all struggle with this, but here's the reality.

577
00:36:46,000 --> 00:36:48,000
 Sin is one of the reasons why we struggle with this,

578
00:36:48,000 --> 00:36:52,000
 because Jesus had no sin, therefore there was no deceit,

579
00:36:52,000 --> 00:36:56,000
 no slander, no gossip, no malice, no brokenness coming out of his mouth.

580
00:36:56,000 --> 00:37:01,000
 When we deal with sin in the source, we begin to find our language change.

581
00:37:01,000 --> 00:37:06,000
 But the reality is so many of us try to change the language and ignore the heart.

582
00:37:06,000 --> 00:37:07,000
 Come on, church.

583
00:37:07,000 --> 00:37:10,000
 We try to change what we're saying,

584
00:37:10,000 --> 00:37:13,000
 thinking that that's the thing that James is calling us to.

585
00:37:13,000 --> 00:37:16,000
 James is like, "I'm not asking you to change what you say.

586
00:37:16,000 --> 00:37:19,000
 I'm asking you to change your heart, and when you change your heart,

587
00:37:19,000 --> 00:37:23,000
 look at what you're about to say."

588
00:37:23,000 --> 00:37:27,000
 Some of you here, you're spending a lot of time trying to get better at what you say

589
00:37:27,000 --> 00:37:30,000
 without spending any time asking the question,

590
00:37:30,000 --> 00:37:35,000
 "Why am I saying the things that I'm saying in the first place?"

591
00:37:35,000 --> 00:37:37,000
 That's the heart.

592
00:37:37,000 --> 00:37:40,000
 Like, "What really is going on in my heart?"

593
00:37:40,000 --> 00:37:42,000
 And so during worship, God's convicting me,

594
00:37:42,000 --> 00:37:47,000
 "Andrew, your anchor's too short."

595
00:37:47,000 --> 00:37:50,000
 A lot of you have submitted to me, but there's still bits of you that are not submitted to me.

596
00:37:50,000 --> 00:37:54,000
 You need to deal with that stuff.

597
00:37:54,000 --> 00:37:58,000
 The health of my heart will determine the grace of my words.

598
00:37:58,000 --> 00:38:00,000
 It'll be the same for you too.

599
00:38:00,000 --> 00:38:02,000
 I don't know about you, but I want to align to the right side.

600
00:38:02,000 --> 00:38:05,000
 So that means I need to deal with the sin.

601
00:38:05,000 --> 00:38:08,000
 God's given us this grace of forgiveness and repentance.

602
00:38:08,000 --> 00:38:12,000
 He's given us the ability to let go of the things that darken our hearts.

603
00:38:12,000 --> 00:38:16,000
 And I want to encourage you, if you're finding yourself aligning more with that evil side,

604
00:38:16,000 --> 00:38:19,000
 even though you know you don't want to, but you find yourself doing it,

605
00:38:19,000 --> 00:38:22,000
 the way you speak to your spouse, the way you speak to your children,

606
00:38:22,000 --> 00:38:24,000
 the way you speak to your colleagues, you know it's not right.

607
00:38:24,000 --> 00:38:26,000
 The question I think the Lord would ask you to is,

608
00:38:26,000 --> 00:38:28,000
 "Just check your heart. What's going on?

609
00:38:28,000 --> 00:38:31,000
 Is there some stuff there that may need to be brought to Him

610
00:38:31,000 --> 00:38:34,000
 in repentance and His grace to forgive you?"

611
00:38:34,000 --> 00:38:36,000
 So that's sin.

612
00:38:36,000 --> 00:38:39,000
 Let me finish on hurt.

613
00:38:39,000 --> 00:38:41,000
 Because I said earlier, hurting people hurt people.

614
00:38:41,000 --> 00:38:45,000
 And while sin is one of the things that causes the bad stuff to come out of our mouths,

615
00:38:45,000 --> 00:38:54,000
 hurt perhaps even more causes us to not be the people that we were created to be.

616
00:38:54,000 --> 00:38:57,000
 Some of you here have been deeply hurt.

617
00:38:57,000 --> 00:38:59,000
 Deeply hurt by words spoken of you.

618
00:38:59,000 --> 00:39:01,000
 Some of it, it's generational.

619
00:39:01,000 --> 00:39:04,000
 Something was spoken over you as a child, and now that you're a parent,

620
00:39:04,000 --> 00:39:08,000
 you're finding yourself speaking the same thing over your child.

621
00:39:08,000 --> 00:39:11,000
 And you know that that's not right, and you feel the shame of it.

622
00:39:11,000 --> 00:39:14,000
 But the reality is you haven't been able to break that cycle.

623
00:39:14,000 --> 00:39:19,000
 Many of us here probably have struggled with the reality that we've been hurt by something somebody said,

624
00:39:19,000 --> 00:39:22,000
 and it's become flesh, and that flesh is now us,

625
00:39:22,000 --> 00:39:25,000
 and it's the way we think about ourselves now.

626
00:39:25,000 --> 00:39:30,000
 And I want you to know that there are two things that will set you free from hurt

627
00:39:30,000 --> 00:39:32,000
 when you think about it in terms of words.

628
00:39:32,000 --> 00:39:36,000
 And if you're feeling that here, these two things are the most important for you in this message.

629
00:39:36,000 --> 00:39:38,000
 Here's the first thing.

630
00:39:38,000 --> 00:39:43,000
 We need to re-hear the word that God says to us

631
00:39:43,000 --> 00:39:46,000
 so that we're not hearing the word that the enemy says.

632
00:39:46,000 --> 00:39:51,000
 Remember, the enemy comes to Adam and Eve and tries to get them to doubt God's word.

633
00:39:51,000 --> 00:39:55,000
 When we're walking in hurt and finding hurt coming out of our mouths,

634
00:39:55,000 --> 00:39:58,000
 it's because we're doubting the way that we were truly created to be.

635
00:39:58,000 --> 00:40:03,000
 We need to realign the ears of our hearts to hear again what God says to us.

636
00:40:03,000 --> 00:40:08,000
 We need to allow him to debar through the scriptures, through our worship,

637
00:40:08,000 --> 00:40:10,000
 through our community together.

638
00:40:10,000 --> 00:40:16,000
 We need to hear the voice of God say the opposite thing from what the voice of the enemy said.

639
00:40:16,000 --> 00:40:20,000
 So when somebody said to me before that I am not good enough,

640
00:40:20,000 --> 00:40:28,000
 I hear from Jesus, "You are my son and my daughter whom I love, and with you I am well pleased."

641
00:40:28,000 --> 00:40:32,000
 When the enemy has said, "You are never going to amount to anything,"

642
00:40:32,000 --> 00:40:38,000
 I'm hearing from the Lord, "I have put the same spirit that raised Jesus from the dead in you,

643
00:40:38,000 --> 00:40:42,000
 and I've put my passion and my mission in you, and I am setting you free."

644
00:40:42,000 --> 00:40:46,000
 When somebody has told me, "You're ugly," I'm hearing from the Lord,

645
00:40:46,000 --> 00:40:50,000
 "I have fearfully and wonderfully made you, and you are unique.

646
00:40:50,000 --> 00:40:55,000
 There is no one in all of creation that carries the image of God just like you."

647
00:40:55,000 --> 00:40:58,000
 Where the enemy has said that I am a person of shame,

648
00:40:58,000 --> 00:41:02,000
 I hear from Jesus, "You are the righteousness of Christ."

649
00:41:02,000 --> 00:41:06,000
 Come on, church.

650
00:41:06,000 --> 00:41:10,000
 So we have to hear what the Lord is saying to us,

651
00:41:10,000 --> 00:41:14,000
 and believe His word over the words that have been spoken,

652
00:41:14,000 --> 00:41:18,000
 either by people with bad intention, or even by people with good intention,

653
00:41:18,000 --> 00:41:21,000
 that still hurt us. Are you with me?

654
00:41:21,000 --> 00:41:26,000
 But there's a second piece, and I think this piece is actually even more important.

655
00:41:26,000 --> 00:41:30,000
 You see, I think it's not just about hearing what God says to us.

656
00:41:30,000 --> 00:41:34,000
 It's not just about hearing what's in His mouth directed towards us.

657
00:41:34,000 --> 00:41:40,000
 It's also now also about what is in our mouths about us.

658
00:41:40,000 --> 00:41:43,000
 You see, if the issue is this hurt that I'm carrying in my spirit,

659
00:41:43,000 --> 00:41:46,000
 and if that hurt has made flesh in me,

660
00:41:46,000 --> 00:41:50,000
 and I've begun to think of my identity based around that thing,

661
00:41:50,000 --> 00:41:54,000
 then here's the thing. The way that I break that reality of that identity,

662
00:41:54,000 --> 00:41:56,000
 yes, it's hearing what God says to me,

663
00:41:56,000 --> 00:41:59,000
 but it's also now prophetically declaring with my own tongue

664
00:41:59,000 --> 00:42:03,000
 that I am not what that word said that I was.

665
00:42:03,000 --> 00:42:08,000
 That I now also can take a stand like Adam standing before the animals

666
00:42:08,000 --> 00:42:11,000
 and saying lion and alligator and giraffe.

667
00:42:11,000 --> 00:42:15,000
 I get to stand before myself and say, "I'm a son of God."

668
00:42:15,000 --> 00:42:20,000
 Like I want to hear God say it, but I need to confess it with my tongue.

669
00:42:20,000 --> 00:42:25,000
 I need to speak out with my mouth because that's going to change something within me.

670
00:42:25,000 --> 00:42:29,000
 So I declare lion. I declare son of God.

671
00:42:29,000 --> 00:42:31,000
 I declare righteousness of Christ.

672
00:42:31,000 --> 00:42:35,000
 I declare that the same spirit in me is the spirit that raised Jesus from the dead.

673
00:42:35,000 --> 00:42:38,000
 And I say it. It's my confession.

